title: Use golden files for extract_computations tree_transformations_test
all_text:
Use golden files for extract_computations tree_transformations_testUse golden files for extract_computations tree_transformations_test

Editing these transformations can cause significant ripple effects
to these outputs which are very annoying to fix up by hand. This
change moves them to use golden files so that the outputs can
be easily automatically updated.

title: Add support for multiple losses with tf.keras
all_text:
Add support for multiple losses with tf.kerasFixes #386 ```suggestion
  def __init__(self, inner_model, dummy_batch, loss_fns, loss_weights=None, metrics=None):
```

Lets add defaults for everything after `loss_fns````suggestion
``````suggestion
``````suggestion
      be the sum of all individual losses, each weighted by `loss_weights`.
``````suggestion
  if isinstance(loss, (collections.Mapping, collections.Sequence)):
```TFF generally aims to include the parameters in the error string for easier debugging, this is probably different than traditional Python.

In this case, perhaps we could add the string `'loss: {}\noutputs: {}'.format(loss, keras_model.outputs)`. Same fro the error raised below.TFF tries to be strict and avoid assumptions on user input. Lets change this to raise an error instead, and include the names of the outputs and losses so the user can easily determine what was missing.Is `yapf` adding the newlines before each new condition branch? This isn't common in TFF, if possible lets remove the empty newlines.Lets add one more test with a dict of loss_weights that doesn't have the same keys are the outputs.
